Column.Title: TEST_ID
Column.Comment: Column with the Actual test number(i.e.1,2..) MANDATORY

Column.Title: TEST_STEP_ID
Column.Comment: Column having the Test step ID for the current test(Sequenced in number, Can't skip the sequence for one particular test Id) MANDATORY

Column.Title: TEST_STEP_TYPE
Column.Comment: Should be the test purpose. eg: GET|SOURCE_QUERY|PRODUCER|TARGET_QUERY MANDATORY

Column.Title: TEST_COMMAND
Column.Comment: As Required for executing the preceding step id for test case, IF GET - LUNAME(MANDATORY);INSTANCE_ID(MANDATORY) || IF PRODUCER - sql Statement(MANDATORY);LUNAME(MANDATORY) || IF SOURCE_QUERY - Source Interface(MANDATORY);Source sql Statement(MANDATORY); Produce ind(MANDATORY)(True if need to produce trx to kafka, else false);LUNAME - If Produce ind is true and LU NAME was not provided then LU NAME from last get is used, If Produce ind is true and no previous Get before this step then LU NAME is mandatory. If Produce ind is true and LU NAME input provided it will always be used. || IF TARGET QUERY - Interface(MANDATORY);Select sql(MANDATORY)

Column.Title: EXPECTED_RESULT
Column.Comment: EXPECTED_JSON output based on the last step from TEST_COMMAND(MANDATORY - If user wants to validate TARGET QUERY).
